    <field name="abstract_teim">The collection contains the papers of Mark Naison, including correspondence, typescripts, publications, student work, research files, organizational records, and photographs, dating from 1931 to 2011. On the whole, they document his life as a student, teacher, historian, writer, activist, and sports enthusiast. Naison, who was born and resided in Brooklyn for most of his life, is a professor of African and African American Studies at Fordham University.</field>
